ta-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526656\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 03, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104cwt1665702749016.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cwt1665702749016.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cwt1665702749016.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"cwt1665702749016\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Returning Network Cloud-Served\n      Licenses </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"cwt1665702749016__returning_cloud_served_network_licenses_203302\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cwt1665702749016__p_d67160e1_d67161e1_d67162e1\">You may wish to return a network cloud-served license to\n         use it on a different Sentinel RMS License Manager.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cwt1665702749016__p_d67163e1_d67164e1_d67165e1\">To return a license, you can either:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cwt1665702749016__li_d29819e1_d29820e1_d29821e1\">Run the RMS License Manager uninstall script. For instructions on how to do this, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dhe1665702749084.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dhe1665702749084.html\">Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows</a> or <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"luh1665702748423.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/luh1665702748423.html\" title=\"To uninstall the RMS License Manager, use the uninstall script that was created in the directory you specified during installation. You will be asked to return your license so that you can use it on a different machine.\">Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix</a>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"cwt1665702749016__li_d29822e1_d29823e1_d29824e1\">Run the Uniface License Management utility (<span class=\"ph filepath\">ulic</span>) from the command line with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ret</span> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntitlementId</var>} command. This utility is provided in the RMS installation folder. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qgt1690346679212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qgt1690346679212.html\" title=\"The Uniface License Management utility (ulic) is responsible for activating and downloading required Sentinel licenses, for checking out licenses, and renewing the lease on licenses on a regular basis. The licenses themselves are maintained by the Sentinel Cloud Server.\">Uniface License Management Utility (ulic)</a>.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 552px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/paz1665702747377.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Sentinel RMS License Manager</a></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cjh1665702747666.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Installing the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows</a><p>The Sentinel Rights Management System (RMS) License Manager enforces and manages licenses for Uniface in multi-user environments.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/frp1665702749898.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows</a></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dhe1665702749084.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows</a></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fnb1665702748208.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Installing the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux</a><p>The Sentinel Rights Management System (RMS) License Manager (also known as the RMS Server) enforces and manages licenses for Uniface in multi-user environments.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mjb1665702748492.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux</a><p>Use the installation script to update or upgrade an older version of the RMS License Manager and the Cloud Plug-in, or to switch license type from a cloud-served license to a license file or license code (or vice versa).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/luh1665702748423.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix</a><p>To uninstall the RMS License Manager, use the uninstall script that was created in the directory you specified during installation. You will be asked to return your license so that you can use it on a different machine.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qhf1665702748352.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Starting and Stopping the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux</a><p>To start or stop the RMS License Manager, use the following commands.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526656\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526656\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Returning Network Cloud-Served Licenses Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 03, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Returning Network Cloud-Served Licenses You may wish to return a network cloud-served license to use it on a different Sentinel RMS License Manager. To return a license, you can either: Run the RMS License Manager uninstall script. For instructions on how to do this, see Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows or Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix . Run the Uniface License Management utility ( ulic ) from the command line with the /ret { EntitlementId } command. This utility is provided in the RMS installation folder. For more information, see Uniface License Management Utility (ulic) . Related Links Sentinel RMS License Manager Installing the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows The Sentinel Rights Management System (RMS) License Manager enforces and manages licenses for Uniface in multi-user environments. Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows Installing the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux The Sentinel Rights Management System (RMS) License Manager (also known as the RMS Server) enforces and manages licenses for Uniface in multi-user environments. Updating the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux Use the installation script to update or upgrade an older version of the RMS License Manager and the Cloud Plug-in, or to switch license type from a cloud-served license to a license file or license code (or vice versa). Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix To uninstall the RMS License Manager, use the uninstall script that was created in the directory you specified during installation. You will be asked to return your license so that you can use it on a different machine. Starting and Stopping the Sentinel RMS License Manager on Unix and Linux To start or stop the RMS License Manager, use the following commands. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}